<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2008</DATELINE><TITLE>Severe Infections in the Returning Traveler</TITLE><BODY>The ease of air travel has made spread of infectious agents a global problem. There are a multitude of tropical diseases ranging from benign viral illnesses to highly contagious and life-threatening diseases and it is important to take a detailed clinical and travel history from the ill returning traveller, especially in the fi rst 4 weeks of return.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>